  "prompt": "I see roads on the Pok\u00e9mon GO map that glow faintly and are lighter, almost white. What is that?",
  "response": "The faintly glowing, almost white roads that you see on the Pok\u00e9mon GO map are part of the Niantic Wayfarer integration. They represent pedestrian pathways, indicating areas that are safe and accessible for walking. These pathways are included to help players navigate more easily and encourage walking, making it more convenient to explore and interact with Pok\u00e9stops, Gyms, and other in-game locations.",
